# Deliberately minimal library — just a `print` primitive.
# Everything else (heading, quote, todo) is declared by the SOURCE
# via `define ... end` blocks. See script.capy.
#
# The point: source files can extend the library's grammar inline,
# without needing the library author to add new patterns.
extension md

function print
    arg literal "print"
    arg capture text string
    template:
        {{ .text | unquote }}

end
